utogenerated1\">{{Cite web|url=https://support.apple.com/kb/SP808?locale=en_US|title=Apple Watch Series 5 - Technical Specifications|website=support.apple.com|access-date=2019-09-19}}</ref>\n|-\n!\"Siri Speaks\" and \"Raise to Speak\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT205184|title=Use Siri on your Apple Watch|website=Apple Support|language=en|access-date=2019-09-19}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"3\" |No\n| colspan=\"3\" |Yes\n|-\n!Display<ref name=\"appleWatchCompare\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" |[[OLED]] Retina display with [[Force Touch]] (450&nbsp;[[Nit (unit)|nits]])<ref name=\"appleWatch0TS\" /><ref name=\"appleWatchCompareArchived\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" |Second-generation OLED Retina display with Force Touch (1000&nbsp;nits)<ref name=\"appleWatchCompareArchived\" /><ref name=\"appleWatch3TS\" /><ref name=\"appleWatchCompare\" />\n|LTPO<ref name=\"OLED-infoLTPOBackplaneTech\">{{cite web|url=https://www.oled-info.com/ltpo|title=LTPO backplane technology - introduction and news|date=February 10, 2019|website=OLED-info|publisher=Metalgrass Ltd.|accessdate=February 27, 2019}}</ref> OLED Retina display with Force Touch (1000&nbsp;nits)<ref name=\"appleWatchCompare\" />\n|LTPO OLED Always-on Retina display with Force Touch (1000 nits)<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n!Pixel Density\n| colspan=\"6\" |326 ppi\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Display Size\n| colspan=\"4\" |38mm (case height): 1.337in (diagonal) with 272x340 pixels<ref name=\"appleHigWatchDisplaySizes\">{{Cite web|url=https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/watchos/visual-design/display-sizes/|title=Display Sizes - Visual Design - watchOS - Human Interface Guidelines - Apple Developer|website=Apple|access-date=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" |40mm (case height): 1.533in (diagonal) with 324x394 pixels<ref name=\"appleHigWatchDisplaySizes\" /> (viewable area reduced by rounded corners)\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" |42mm (case height): 1.566in (diagonal) with 312x390 pixels<ref name=\"appleHigWatchDispl