B DRAM<ref name=\"Lanaria\" />\n|-\n!OS Versions\n|[[watchOS]] 1 to 4<ref name=\"appleWatch0TS\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" |watchOS 3 to 6<ref name=\"appleWatchOS5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/watchos/watchos-preview/|title=watchOS 6 compatibility}}</ref>\n|watchOS 4 to 6<ref name=\"appleWatchOS5\" />\n|watchOS 5 to 6<ref name=\"appleWatchOS5\" />\n|watchOS 6\n|-\n!Requires{{ref|A|[A]}}\n|[[iPhone 5]] or later running [[iOS 8.2]] or later<ref name=\"appleWatch0TS\" />\n| colspan=\"2\" |iPhone 5 or later running [[iOS 10]] or later<ref name=\"applePR_AWS2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2016/09/apple-introduces-apple-watch-series-2.html|title=Apple introduces Apple Watch Series 2|publisher=}}</ref>\n|'''Non-LTE''': [[iPhone 5S]] or later running [[iOS 11]] or later<ref name=\"appleWatch3TS\" /><br />'''LTE''': [[iPhone 6]] or later, running iOS 11 or later<ref name=\"appleWatch3TS\" />\n|'''Non-LTE''': [[iPhone 5S]] or later running [[iOS 12]] or later<ref name=\"appleWatch4TS\" /><br />'''LTE''': [[iPhone 6]] or later, running iOS 12 or later<ref name=\"appleWatchCompare\" />\n|[[IPhone 6S|iPhone 6s]] or later, running [[iOS 13]] or later\n|-\n!Battery\n| colspan=\"2\" |205&nbsp;[[MAh|mA\u00b7h]], 3.8&nbsp;[[V]], 0.78&nbsp;[[Watt-hour|W\u00b7h]] battery capacity (38&nbsp;mm){{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n250&nbsp;mA\u00b7h, 3.78&nbsp;V, 0.93&nbsp;W\u00b7h battery capacity (42&nbsp;mm){{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n|273&nbsp;mA\u00b7h, 3.77&nbsp;V, 1.03&nbsp;W\u00b7h battery capacity (38&nbsp;mm){{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\n334&nbsp;mA\u00b7h, 3.80&nbsp;V, 1.27&nbsp;W\u00b7h battery capacity (42&nbsp;mm){{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n|'''Non-LTE''': 262&nbsp;mA\u00b7h, 3.81&nbsp;V, 1.00&nbsp;W\u00b7h battery capacity (38&nbsp;mm)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ifixit.com/Store/Smartwatch/Apple-Watch-38-mm-Series-3-GPS-Replacement-Battery/IF374-016?o=2|title=Apple Watch (38 mm Series 3 GPS) Replacement Battery 